      • registeredListeners

        private Map<org.bukkit.event.Listener,Boolean> registeredListeners
        Stores the flag listeners that have already been registered into Bukkit's API to avoid duplicates. Value is true if the listener has been registered already. This helps to make sure each flag listener is loaded correctly.
        See Also:
        registerListeners()

        public boolean registerFlag(@NonNull Flag flag)
        Registers a new flag. Consider using registerFlag(Addon, Flag) instead if your flag declares a listener.
        Parameters:
        flag - flag to be registered
        Returns:
        true if successfully registered, false if not, e.g., because one with the same ID already exists
        See Also:
